entry.title: [Rounded Windows] Round the ghost surface
entry.content:
Once an ARC++ application is launched, while ARC++ is being loaded and

initialized, we show a ghost surface that shows a loading animation.



Specifying the window radii using the API introduced in the CL:

crrev.com/c/4775627 will not round the ghost surface. Ghost surface

is an overlay widget for the shell_surface where that API only rounds

the content of root_surface and window header.



Therefore we need to handle ghost surface separately. We round the

bottom two corners of ghost overlay content using cc rounding API.

entry.content:
automatically

of size 8 or greater is present, the function gets the stack

protector prologue and epilogue added.



For reasons old as time, we set it to 4, which triggers

an interesting LLVM bug: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/66709



The result of this bug was increased binary size with stack

protector added on functions that do not need it. The compiler

mistakenly counts structure padding as a local array, and adds

the stack protector. With the default of 8 set by this CL,

the unnecessary addition will not normally happen, since the

padding size added to structures will be smaller than 8.



The result will be a decreased binary size (-272K on

android-binary-size).

entry.title: infra: Support links to mirrored/mirroring builders in descriptions
entry.content:
This should allow a viewer to easily map between a CI bot and any try

bot that mirrors it (or vice versa), so long as the builders

involved have migrated their recipe configs to starlark. (We assume

most every chromium bot has.)



And this enables the new descriptions for only builders mirroring

or being mirrored by "GPU FYI Mac Builder". This builder has a lot of

mirrors (see the cr-buildbucket.cfg diff). So we assume it's a good

check of how the descriptions will look. Will expand to all builders

if it looks good.



Note that with the completion of crbug.com/1344925, the description

should be stored on a per-build basis. Meaning: if the description

changes, the description displayed on older builds will still show the

description that was live when the build ran. This is preferred since

it enables us to store somewhat volatile information in the

description. But that may confuse folks if they read the description

from old builds and assume it applies to the builder now. Not sure

how to resolve that. (Maybe show a warning in milo if the old

description != current description?)



Without this change, main.star takes about 3.23s locally. With it, it

takes about 3.28s. (That's the average across 10 runs.)

entry.content:
When an additional bid wins an auction, the auction reports this win to

the buyer via a function that has a slightly different name than the one

that would be called to report the win of a bid created by a call to

generateBid(). This is described in more detail at

https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#64-reporting-additional-bid-wins.



This change renames this function from reportContextualWin to

reportAdditionalBidWin for consistency, since the term additional bid is

used throughout the auction, including in the header used to transport

it (Ad-Auction-Additional-Bid) and the field on the auction config

(additionalBids).

entry.title: Optimize python test code for large numbers of virtual tests
entry.content:
Adding large numbers of virtual tests is exposing inefficiencies in the

virtual test suite infrastructure. This patch adds a few simple

optimizations which virtually (ha!) eliminates the overhead of

additional virtual WPT tests in https://crrev.com/c/4766359 [1]:

* lookup_virtual_test_base, _wpt_test_urls_matching_paths, and

normalize_test_name have been memoized.

* An expensive step to remove empty path components in

_wpt_test_urls_matching_paths has been inlined into all_urls().

* get_expectations.* has been memoized.

* The loop over exclusive test in skipped_due_to_exclusive_virtual_tests

has been optimized.



[1] Data from linux-rel tryjob runs on https://crrev.com/c/4874857

(baseline), https://crrev.com/c/4874645 (extra tests), and

https://crrev.com/c/4875966 (extra tests + this patch).
